[src:statistics-fundamentals/central-limit-theorem] However, the distribution of *c*1*X*1 + ⋯ + *cnXn* is close to ${\textstyle {\mathcal {N}}(0,1)}$ (in the total variation distance) for most vectors (*c*1, ..., *cn*) according to the uniform distribution on the sphere *c*2 1 + ⋯ + *c*2 *n* = 1.
